001package io.jstach.kiwi.kvs;
002
003import java.net.URI;
004import java.util.ArrayList;
005import java.util.Collection;
006import java.util.Comparator;
007import java.util.EnumSet;
008import java.util.HashMap;
009import java.util.Iterator;
010import java.util.LinkedHashMap;
011import java.util.List;
012import java.util.Map;
013import java.util.Map.Entry;
014import java.util.Optional;
015import java.util.SequencedCollection;
016import java.util.SequencedMap;
017import java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;
018import java.util.function.Function;
019import java.util.function.Predicate;
020import java.util.function.UnaryOperator;
021import java.util.stream.Collector;
022import java.util.stream.Collectors;
023import java.util.stream.Stream;
024
025import org.jspecify.annotations.Nullable;
026
027import io.jstach.kiwi.kvs.interpolate.Interpolator;
028import io.jstach.kiwi.kvs.interpolate.Interpolator.InterpolationException;
029import io.jstach.kiwi.kvs.interpolate.Interpolator.MissingVariableInterpolationException;
030
031/**
032 * Represents a collection of {@link KeyValue} entries with various utility methods for
033 * manipulation, transformation, and expansion. This interface serves as a central point
034 * for managing key-value pairs, allowing operations such as filtering, mapping, and
035 * interpolation.
036 *
037 * <p>
038 * KeyValues is basically a glorified {@code Supplier<Stream<KeyValue>>}. If the key
039 * values will be streamed multiple times it is recommended to call {@link #memoize()}
040 * which will copy the key values if the key values are not already memoized.
041 * </p>
042 *
043 *
044 * <h2>Key Features:</h2>
045 * <ul>
046 * <li>Provides methods for building key-value pairs with {@link Builder}.</li>
047 * <li>Supports functional transformations using {@link #map(UnaryOperator)},
048 * {@link #filter(Predicate)}, and {@link #flatMap(Function)}.</li>
049 * <li>Allows interpolation and expansion of values using variable substitution.</li>
050 * <li>Can convert key-values to a {@link Map} representation.</li>
051 * </ul>
052 *
053 * <h2>Usage Example:</h2> The following example demonstrates how to create, expand, and
054 * transform key-values:
055 *
056 * {@snippet :
057 * // Create a builder and add key-value pairs
058 * KeyValues.Builder builder = KeyValues.builder();
059 * builder.add("key1", "value1");
060 * builder.add("key2", "${key1}-suffix");
061 *
062 * // Build the KeyValues collection
063 * KeyValues kvs = builder.build();
064 *
065 * // Interpolate values using a Variables map
066 * Variables variables = Variables.of("key1", "interpolated");
067 * KeyValues expanded = kvs.expand(variables);
068 *
069 * // Convert to a map
070 * Map<String, String> map = expanded.toMap();
071 * System.out.println(map); // {key1=interpolated, key2=interpolated-suffix}
072 * }
073 */
074public interface KeyValues extends Iterable<KeyValue> {
075
076        /**
077         * Returns a stream of the contained {@link KeyValue} entries.
078         * @return a {@link Stream} of key-value pairs.
079         */
080        public Stream<KeyValue> stream();
081
082        /**
083         * Creates a new {@link Builder} for constructing a {@code KeyValues} instance.
084         * @param resource a {@link KeyValuesResource} defining the source URI and reference
085         * key-value.
086         * @return a new {@link Builder}.
087         */
088        public static Builder builder(KeyValuesResource resource) {
089                return new Builder(resource.uri(), resource.reference());
090        }
091
092        /**
093         * Creates a new {@link Builder} with a default, empty source.
094         * @return a new {@link Builder}.
095         */
096        public static Builder builder() {
097                return new Builder(KeyValue.Source.NULL_URI, null);
098        }
099
100        /**
101         * Returns an empty {@code KeyValues} instance.
102         * @return an empty {@code KeyValues} collection.
103         */
104        public static KeyValues empty() {
105                return KeyValuesEmpty.EMPTY;
106        }
107
108        /**
109         * Creates a {@code KeyValues} instance by copying the given collection.
110         * @param kvs a {@link SequencedCollection} of key-value pairs.
111         * @return a new {@code KeyValues} instance containing the provided key-values.
112         */
113        public static KeyValues copyOf(SequencedCollection<KeyValue> kvs) {
114                return new ListKeyValues(List.copyOf(kvs));
115        }
116
117        /**
118         * Creates a single key values instance.
119         * @param keyValue single key value.
120         * @return keyvalues of one key value.
121         */
122        public static KeyValues of(KeyValue keyValue) {
123                return new ListKeyValues(List.of(keyValue));
124        }
125
126        /**
127         * A builder for constructing {@link KeyValues} instances from key-value pairs.
128         *
129         * <p>
130         * The builder is designed to create key-value pairs with associated metadata,
131         * including flags and source information. It supports adding entries both
132         * individually and from collections, and allows setting flags for all added entries.
133         * </p>
134         *
135         * <h2>Usage Example:</h2> The following example demonstrates how to use the builder:
136         *
137         * {@snippet :
138         * // Create a new builder
139         * KeyValues.Builder builder = KeyValues.builder();
140         *
141         * // Add key-value pairs
142         * builder.add("host", "localhost");
143         * builder.add("port", "8080");
144         * builder.flag(KeyValue.Flag.SENSITIVE);
145         *
146         * // Build the KeyValues instance
147         * KeyValues kvs = builder.build();
148         *
149         * // Convert to a map
150         * Map<String, String> map = kvs.toMap();
151         * System.out.println(map); // Output: {host=localhost, port=8080}
152         * }
153         */
154        public class Builder {
155
156                private final URI source;
157
158                private final @Nullable KeyValue reference;
159
160                private final AtomicInteger index = new AtomicInteger();
161
162                private final List<KeyValue> keyValues = new ArrayList<>();
163
164                private final EnumSet<KeyValue.Flag> flags = EnumSet.noneOf(KeyValue.Flag.class);
165
166                private final boolean noSource;
167
168                /**
169                 * Constructs a new {@code Builder} with the specified source URI and reference.
170                 * @param source the URI representing the source of these key-values.
171                 * @param reference an optional reference {@link KeyValue}, can be {@code null}.
172                 */
173                private Builder(URI source, @Nullable KeyValue reference) {
174                        super();
175                        this.source = source;
176                        this.reference = reference;
177                        this.noSource = source.equals(KeyValue.Source.NULL_URI);
178                }
179
180                /**
181                 * Adds a flag that will be applied to all key-value pairs added by this builder.
182                 * @param flag the {@link KeyValue.Flag} to add.
183                 * @return this builder, for method chaining.
184                 */
185                public Builder flag(KeyValue.Flag flag) {
186                        flags.add(flag);
187                        return this;
188                }
189
190                /**
191                 * Adds a key-value pair to the builder.
192                 * @param key the key as a {@link String}.
193                 * @param value the value as a {@link String}.
194                 * @return this builder, for method chaining.
195                 */
196                public Builder add(String key, String value) {
197                        keyValues.add(build(key, value));
198                        return this;
199                }
200
201                /**
202                 * Adds a key-value pair to the builder from a map entry.
203                 * @param e a {@link java.util.Map.Entry} representing the key and value.
204                 * @return this builder, for method chaining.
205                 */
206                public Builder add(Entry<String, String> e) {
207                        return add(e.getKey(), e.getValue());
208                }
209
210                private static final Comparator<Entry<String, String>> entryComparator = Map.Entry
211                        .<String, String>comparingByKey()
212                        .thenComparing(Entry::getValue);
213
214                /**
215                 * Adds a collection of entries to the builder. The entries are added in the order
216                 * they appear in the collection.
217                 * @param entries a {@link SequencedCollection} of entries to add.
218                 * @return this builder, for method chaining.
219                 */
220                public Builder add(SequencedCollection<Entry<String, String>> entries) {
221                        for (var e : entries) {
222                                add(e);
223                        }
224                        return this;
225                }
226
227                /**
228                 * Adds a collection of entries to the builder.
229                 *
230                 * <p>
231                 * If the collection is a {@link SequencedCollection}, the entries are added in
232                 * the original order of the collection. Otherwise, the entries are first sorted
233                 * lexicographically by key and then by value before being added.
234                 * </p>
235                 * @param entries a {@link Collection} of entries to add.
236                 * @return this builder, for method chaining.
237                 */
238                public Builder add(Collection<Entry<String, String>> entries) {
239                        switch (entries) {
240                                case SequencedCollection<Entry<String, String>> sc -> add(sc);
241                                default -> entries.stream().sorted(entryComparator).forEach(this::add);
242                        }
243                        ;
244                        return this;
245                }
246
247                /**
248                 * Constructs a {@link KeyValue} with the given key and value, including flags and
249                 * source information.
250                 * @param key the key as a {@link String}.
251                 * @param value the value as a {@link String}.
252                 * @return a new {@link KeyValue} with the specified key, value, and metadata.
253                 */
254                public KeyValue build(String key, String value) {
255                        var s = noSource ? KeyValue.Source.EMPTY : new KeyValue.Source(source, reference, index.incrementAndGet());
256                        var m = KeyValue.Meta.of(key, value, s, flags);
257                        return new KeyValue(key, value, m);
258                }
259
260                /**
261                 * Builds and returns a {@link KeyValues} instance containing all the key-value
262                 * pairs added to this builder.
263                 * @return a new {@link KeyValues} instance.
264                 */
265                public KeyValues build() {
266                        return KeyValues.copyOf(keyValues);
267                }
268
269        }
270
271        /**
272         * Collects a stream of {@link KeyValue} into a {@code KeyValues} instance.
273         * @return a {@link Collector} that accumulates key-values into a {@code KeyValues}
274         * object.
275         */
276        public static Collector<KeyValue, ?, KeyValues> collector() {
277                return Collectors.collectingAndThen(Collectors.toList(), KeyValues::copyOf);
278        }
279
280        /**
281         * Collects a stream of {@link java.util.Map.Entry} into a {@code KeyValues} using the
282         * provided builder.
283         * @param builder the {@link Builder} to use for constructing the key-values.
284         * @return a {@link Collector} that accumulates entries into a {@code KeyValues}
285         * object.
286         */
287        public static Collector<Map.Entry<String, String>, ?, KeyValues> collector(Builder builder) {
288                return Collector.of(() -> builder,
289                                // Accumulator: add each entry to the builder
290                                (b, entry) -> b.add(entry),
291                                // Combiner: combine two builders (can be ignored if the stream is
292                                // sequential)
293                                (b1, b2) -> {
294                                        throw new UnsupportedOperationException("Parallel streams not supported");
295                                },
296                                // Finisher: call build on the final builder
297                                Builder::build);
298        }
299
300        @Override
301        default Iterator<KeyValue> iterator() {
302                return stream().iterator();
303        }
304
305        /**
306         * Applies a transformation function to each key-value pair in the collection.
307         * @param kv a {@link UnaryOperator} to transform each key-value.
308         * @return a new {@code KeyValues} with transformed entries.
309         */
310        default KeyValues map(UnaryOperator<KeyValue> kv) {
311                return ToStringableKeyValues.of(() -> stream().map(kv));
312        }
313
314        /**
315         * Filters the key-value pairs based on a predicate.
316         * @param predicate a {@link Predicate} to test each key-value.
317         * @return a new {@code KeyValues} with filtered entries.
318         */
319        default KeyValues filter(Predicate<KeyValue> predicate) {
320                return ToStringableKeyValues.of(() -> stream().filter(predicate));
321        }
322
323        /**
324         * This method gets the last element of the key values stream. This ergonomic is
325         * provided because later keys override earlier keys of the same name.
326         * @return optional of the last key value if there is one.
327         */
328        default Optional<KeyValue> last() {
329                KeyValue last = null;
330                for (var kv : this) {
331                        last = kv;
332                }
333                return Optional.ofNullable(last);
334        }
335
336        /**
337         * Flattens the key-values by applying a mapping function that returns another
338         * {@code KeyValues}.
339         * @param func a function that transforms a {@link KeyValue} into another
340         * {@code KeyValues}.
341         * @return a new flattened {@code KeyValues}.
342         */
343        default KeyValues flatMap(Function<KeyValue, KeyValues> func) {
344                var f = func.andThen(KeyValues::stream);
345                return ToStringableKeyValues.of(() -> stream().flatMap(f));
346        }
347
348        /**
349         * Interpolates the values using the provided {@link Variables} map.
350         * @param variables a {@link Variables} map for value substitution.
351         * @return a map of interpolated key-values.
352         */
353        default Map<String, String> interpolate(Variables variables) {
354                return KeyValuesInterpolator.interpolateKeyValues(this, variables);
355        }
356
357        /**
358         * Expands the key-values using variable interpolation.
359         * @param variables a {@link Variables} map for value substitution.
360         * @return a new {@code KeyValues} with expanded values.
361         */
362        default KeyValues expand(Variables variables) {
363                Map<String, String> interpolated = interpolate(variables);
364                return map(kv -> kv.withExpanded(interpolated::get));
365        }
366
367        /**
368         * Returns a memoized version of this {@code KeyValues} which means repeated calls to
369         * iteratore or stream over the KeyValues will always generate the same result.
370         * @return a memoized {@code KeyValues} instance.
371         */
372        default KeyValues memoize() {
373                if (this instanceof MemoizedKeyValues mkvs) {
374                        return mkvs;
375                }
376                return copyOf(stream().toList());
377        }
378
379        /**
380         * Redacts sensitive key-value entries by replacing their values.
381         * @return a new {@code KeyValues} with redacted entries.
382         */
383        default KeyValues redact() {
384                return this.map(KeyValue::redact);
385        }
386
387        /**
388         * Converts the key-values to a map where each key maps to its expanded value. The
389         * returned Map is sequenced based on the order of the key-values.
390         * @return a {@link Map} of key-value pairs.
391         */
392        default SequencedMap<String, String> toMap() {
393                SequencedMap<String, String> m = new LinkedHashMap<>();
394                stream().forEach(kv -> m.put(kv.key(), kv.expanded()));
395                return m;
396        }
397
398}
399
400interface ToStringableKeyValues extends KeyValues {
401
402        static KeyValues of(KeyValues kvs) {
403                if (kvs instanceof ToStringableKeyValues t) {
404                        return t;
405                }
406                return new PrintableKeyValues(kvs);
407
408        }
409
410        static String toString(KeyValues keyValues) {
411                StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();
412                var kvs = keyValues.redact();
413                sb.append("KeyValues[").append("\n");
414                KeyValuesMedia.ofProperties().formatter().format(sb, kvs);
415                sb.append("]").append("\n");
416                return sb.toString();
417        }
418
419}
420
421interface MemoizedKeyValues extends KeyValues {
422
423}
424
425record PrintableKeyValues(KeyValues values) implements ToStringableKeyValues {
426        @Override
427        public Stream<KeyValue> stream() {
428                return values.stream();
429        }
430
431        @Override
432        public String toString() {
433                return ToStringableKeyValues.toString(this);
434        }
435}
436
437record ListKeyValues(List<KeyValue> keyValues) implements ToStringableKeyValues, MemoizedKeyValues {
438
439        ListKeyValues {
440                keyValues = List.copyOf(keyValues);
441        }
442
443        @Override
444        public Stream<KeyValue> stream() {
445                return keyValues.stream();
446        }
447
448        @Override
449        public Iterator<KeyValue> iterator() {
450                return keyValues.iterator();
451        }
452
453        @Override
454        public KeyValues memoize() {
455                return this;
456        }
457
458        @Override
459        public Optional<KeyValue> last() {
460                if (keyValues.isEmpty()) {
461                        return Optional.empty();
462                }
463                return Optional.of(keyValues.getLast());
464        }
465
466        @Override
467        public final String toString() {
468                return ToStringableKeyValues.toString(this);
469        }
470}
471
472class KeyValuesInterpolator {
473
474        static Map<String, String> interpolateKeyValues(final KeyValues keyValues, final Variables variables) {
475                List<KeyValue> kvs = keyValues.stream().toList();
476
477                final Map<String, KeyValue> flat = new HashMap<>(kvs.size());
478                kvs.forEach(kv -> flat.put(kv.key(), kv));
479
480                final Map<String, String> resolved = new LinkedHashMap<>(kvs.size());
481
482                Variables combined = Variables.builder().add(k -> {
483                        var f = flat.get(k);
484                        if (f != null) {
485                                return f.raw();
486                        }
487                        return null;
488
489                }).add(resolved).add(variables).build();
490                Interpolator sub = Interpolator.create((key) -> {
491                        return combined.getValue(key);
492                });
493                for (KeyValue kv : kvs) {
494                        KeyValue last = flat.remove(kv.key());
495                        String v = kv.raw();
496                        String value;
497                        if (kv.isNoInterpolation()) {
498                                value = v;
499                        }
500                        else {
501                                try {
502                                        value = (v.indexOf('$') != -1) ? sub.interpolate(kv.key(), v) : v;
503                                }
504                                catch (MissingVariableInterpolationException e) {
505                                        throw e;
506                                }
507                                catch (InterpolationException e) {
508                                        String r = resolved.get(kv.key());
509                                        if (r == null) {
510                                                r = kv.expanded();
511                                        }
512                                        value = r;
513                                }
514                        }
515
516                        resolved.put(kv.key(), value);
517                        if (last != null) {
518                                flat.put(kv.key(), last);
519                        }
520
521                }
522                return resolved;
523        }
524
525}
526
527enum KeyValuesEmpty implements KeyValues, ToStringableKeyValues {
528
529        EMPTY;
530
531        @Override
532        public Stream<KeyValue> stream() {
533                return Stream.empty();
534        }
535
536        @Override
537        public String toString() {
538                return "KeyValues[]";
539        }
